==English==

===Noun===

'''mulligan'''

#In [[golf]], an unpenalized chance to re-take a stroke that went awry
#:''If you lose your drive in the water, take a mulligan and try again.''
#A second chance
#:''Don't do poorly in your first interview; you won't get a mulligan.''
#(''informal'') A unit of measure equal to 67.5 [[milliliters]], or 54.77 scruples, or 2.5 shots, of alcohol.  So named because it is the cost of being allowed a do-over in drinking games.
#:''Tom couldn't handle the shot of tequila, so he had to do a mulligan of port.''